<p>On the basis of exchange rates  from July 21 - 25, the UK RMG is greater than +5 per cent, at 9.801. It is therefore currently forecast to enter its fourth of a possible five confirmation periods on 31 July. If it remains above +5 per cent for each of the  three remaining 10-day confirmation periods, the UK green rate faces revaluation on 20 August 1997. All currencies with negative RMGs for this period will devalue on 31 July by reducing their gaps to zero. Hence further devaluations are currently forecast for the Belgian, German, Dutch, Danish, French, Spanish, Portuguese and Austrian green rates on 31 July. During confirmation periods the 3-day (6 per cent) rule is suspended.</p>
